In this file we describe how you can use the following algorithms:

a) Ilp-Heur (ILP-based heuristic based on instance reduction) for the LAPCS problem   (*)

b) Hyb-Alg (hybrid algorithm) for the LAPCS problem (**)

(*)(**) Described in the paper "Hybrid Techniques Based on Solving Reduced Problem Instances for a Longest Common Subsequence Problem" by C. Blum and M.J. Blesa (submitted to ASOC)

Ilp-Heur:

 usage: ./Ilp-Heur -i <input_graph> [options]
     options:
            -tlim  float       	  Set the execution time limit in seconds
            -perc  float          Set the reduction percentage [>= 1.0].

Hyb-Alg:

 usage: ./Hyb-Alg -i <input_graph> [options]
    options:
            -sols    	     int     Number of solutions generated by per iteration of Hyb-Alg [>=1]
            -t       	     float   Total admissible running time for Hyb-Alg in seconds
            -drate           float   Set the determinism rate of the probabilistic solution construction mechanism [between 0.0 and 1.0]. 
            -lsize           int     Set the size of candidate list of the probabilistic solution construction mechanism [>= 2].
            -cpltime         float   Set the computation time limit for each CPLEX application 


